    feat(phase1-a2): add fault-type conditioning and expand expert pool
    
    Plan A2 continuation after Gate 1 FAIL.
    
    Changes:
    - Expand expert pool from 4 -> 7 experts:
      ttest, nsigma, cusum, baro, rcd, circa, microcause
    - Expand full_matrix expert presets to include rcd/circa/microcause
    - Add optional fault_type one-hot conditioning (5 dims) to train_router_v2
      and run_gate1_eval without changing the base 18 signal features
    - Add tests for conditioning vector order, unknown fault_type, 23-d input
    - Update learned-router test to track dynamic EXPERTS set
    
    Validation:
    - 43 passed in full pytest suite
    - smoke train with --condition-on-fault-type: softtarget CV 0.8331
    - conditioned Gate 1 smoke (softtarget, 1 seed): 4/25 pass_rule, 7/25 pass_best
    
    This lands the A2 plumbing only; next step is to rerun baseline matrix with the
    expanded expert pool and then re-run Gate 1 for the 7-expert conditioned setup.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

